7:
Right! That's another job done! Once
the client signs off on it, I'm all set.
11:
Having Love along would've made
things go smoother, but she just had
to spout some stuff about
self-improvement and run off to
Starview Village.
13:
It's not like I can't work solo, but...
*sigh* I hope she comes back soon.
Texting's convenient, but it's got its
limits.
17:
Self-improvement, huh... I guess I
should work on myself too. I don't
want to let Love down.
20:
Well, I've got downtime between
jobs, so now's—
25:
Definitely NOT the best time.
Sorry, but you'll have to get up super
early in the morning to get the jump
on me.
30:
Found her! Set your sights, boys—we
bag her and the credits'll be ours!
36:
Who hired you? You're not a
card-carrying member of my fan
club, I know that much.
38:
I don't know the details! The request
came from multiple clients!
40:
A whole bunch of corporations want
your head for destroying the dome
and making their investments
worthless!
43:
I don't suppose you'd all just go
home if I said it was an accident,
huh.
48:
Come on. Are you seriously saying
they sent all of you to catch little old
me? Overkill, don't you think?
51:
That's not the way the corporations
see it.
53:
Those ads are the sacred, inviolable
property of the corporations. It'd be
a PR nightmare if you walked away
without so much as a fine.
56:
That explains why the city's crawling
with troubleshooters. I thought there
was a convention and I didn't get
the memo.
59: A job's a job. But I've gotta know...
61:
Why the hell did you do it? You're not
stupid—you could've seen this
coming a mile off.
69: I did it to see my friend smile!
73:
It's been real, but I've got to jet!
Maybe next time I'll give you an
autograph!
79:
Geez...
That bounty hunter wasn't kidding.
Everyone's out for my blood.
82:
But little do they know, I've got a safe
house that no one can get to.
88:
I wonder what's on the other side. A
postwar dystopian hellscape? A
haunted land with ghouls at every
turn?
91:
...Probably not. I remember how
freaked out Love was when we
played that VR horror game.
96:
Whatever kind of place it is, I'm sure
the sky's a damn sight prettier!
101: Do you have the shopping list, Alk?
104:
Yep! We should be able to get
everything we need in Palpebra...
118:
Whoa, what an awesome town. And
look at that sky! I thought...
125:
I dunno. I thought it'd be a lot closer,
like you could reach out and touch it.
129:
You look starstruck. Or maybe
skystruck is a better word?
132:
I've been dreaming of this moment
for so long! And now I'm finally here!
Looking up at a clear sky!
136:
Please, Stella! You've got to let me
stay here!
137:
My base got smithereened and
there are bounty hunters on my tail...
But none of that matters anymore!
140:
Um, what exactly happened over
there?
145:
Seriously, it's nothing! What's a
busted base and bounty hunters
compared to this beautiful sky?!
149:
Starview Village is a pretty clickbait
name, but the sky's literally FILLED
with stars! And each one's a world of
its own?! That's crazy!
151:
I thought the divine was just
algorithms in the machine, but
looking at this makes me think there
is a higher power out there!
161:
Of course. Welcome to Starview
Village, Buletta.
166:
Seriously?! Whoa... That's so...
Thanks, Stella!
172:
Want to join us for some shopping?
We can buy things for your
welcoming party too!
176:
Or you could stay behind, if you wish
to do some more stargazing.
180:
Nah. I'm happy to help. It's the least I
could do since you're letting me
stay.
184:
I can't wait to start a new life here
with all of you!
